s of Si-rich shrapnel are expected to\noriginate in deeper layers of the progenitor star compared to ejecta with\nlower-Z elements. A high velocity and density contrast with respect to the\nsurrounding ejecta are necessary to make shrapnel A and G overtake the forward\nshock. The line connecting shrapnel A and G crosses almost exactly the\nexpansion center of the remnant, strongly suggesting a Si-rich jet-counterjet\nstructure, reminiscent of that observed in the young remnant Cas A.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 17 Jul 2017 15:15:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-08-02"}
